review_text: Awful staff with ZERO customer empathy, and ZERO common sense. lacking knowledge on basic practices and will not take accountability for any wrongdoing or ignorance. Rude And unprofessiona.
Address online is wrong. Try to call them a phone continually rings. Zero customer service or personality skills. Terrible!

I absolutely love going out of my way to do something that should be simple and find that it cannot be done; don't you???

In West Hartford for Easter and really needed to deposit a check that was in my wallet ("was"... ha!  It's still there!) so after determining that a Citizens ATM was indeed in town, I went a few miles out of my way, parked and tried to go in.

But, what's this??  A 24 hour ATM behind a door that does not open???  Um, what's up with that, Citizens?  Epic Citizens fail... not for the first time, and probably won't be the last (until I switch banks).

Great staff especially when everyone knows your name. Sarah is amazing and very helpful. She opened my account and was very timely about it. I have had nothing but great experience's with all of the staff. I look forward to many years of working with this branch :-)

Terrible bank and service. They sell themselves as being able to handle international transactions, but fail at every turn. You cannot do any type of international activity on the weekend - their staff is not available. Even during the week, they cannot complete a transaction if they can't get hold of the right person. It's a joke, and they've let me down on many occasions. I'm transitioning my account to another bank.

I'm not sure how this branch has received negative ratings. There was confusion on my account and this team cleared it up for me right away - fast, congenial, made my morning. I even got to sit down and talk about my credit score and options for making it stronger. I got so much more than I asked for by stopping in this morning, and it was so much easier - laughably easier - than trying to handle everything on the phone. This is a great branch!
